I&#39;m sitting here minding my own business and i&#39;m dragged into yet another negative post.

This used to be a great group and an original for this field, about 6 years ago before anybody knew about ghost boxes a few of us were here doing our research and posting our stuff.  

Just look in the archives to see the activity we use to have here.  It&#39;s true, i do use this group mainly to allow fellow enthusiasts to own a decent box at a cheap price.  

There are 900 people here to target, although there never is a post anymore.  

Me and others do all of our posting at my RTSC yahoo group, where i help individuals daily with advice and links to FREE downloads and ideas to test and try.

Despite what frank says, i never claimed to invent anything or say he didn&#39;t.  That all came from his brain and it was all made up.

All i did was add a function generator kit for $10 to a radio to make it sweep.  I got the idea from Rich Georgina on my group, that wasn&#39;t my idea either.

All these things are all documented everywhere with me giving all the credit to Bill Chappel, frank, rich, joe.

Somehow franks lies went mainstream about me.  If you don&#39;t believe what i&#39;m saying, i have all this FREE information documented on my site for 6 years now.  I have never made any money off of anybody and i offer everything for Free on my site including all the hacks i did and how to make your own ghost boxes with a sweep circuit.  I even have the links on where to get the parts to build them cheap.

So before you post something else negative, do your homework on who people are and what they have contributed without any fame in mind or monetary motives.

-Steve H.




